        "content": "<p>Wrote those 2 proofs from <em>The Mechanics of Proof</em>. In both cases, I used <code>use</code>. Can I outsource the search to an ATP directly from Lean?</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Proof 1</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>import Mathlib\nimport Lean\n\n example {p q : ℝ} (h : p &lt; q) : ∃ x, p &lt; x ∧ x &lt; q := by\n  use (p + q) / 2\n  constructor\n  · linarith\n  · linarith\n</code></pre></div>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Proof 2</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>import Mathlib\nimport Lean\n\nexample (a : ℤ) : ∃ m n : ℤ, m ^ 2 - n ^ 2 = 2 * a + 1 := by\n  use a+1\n  use a\n  linarith\n</code></pre></div>\n</div></div>\n<p>Also, re-wrote the proof from the book like this:</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>It's a very interesting number</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>example : ∃ a b c d : ℕ,\n    a ^ 3 + b ^ 3 = 1729 ∧ c ^ 3 + d ^ 3 = 1729 ∧ a ≠ c ∧ a ≠ d := by\n  use 1, 12, 9, 10\n  exact ⟨by norm_num, by norm_num, by norm_num, by norm_num⟩\n</code></pre></div>\n</div></div>",
